                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123G98/35a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Emperor of Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I thank Your Majesty for your courteous and highly appreciated message of
                    sympathy on the death of Mr. Guthrie, by whose demise the United States loses a
                    valued citizen and Japan a sincere and constant friend, and whose lasting
                    monument, I trust, will be the perpetuity of the present cordial relations and
                    good understanding between the United States and Japan which he did so much to
                    promote and had so much at heart.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
